With them AG, killing off those birds, haha! now watch them complain come  
this summer, when we have a massive bug out break, those are the very kind 
of  birds that maintain the bugs in lower populations, they eat the flying  
bugs!  Grackles, Red Wings, they eat bugs, they keep the mosquitoes in  check 
too.  We will probably have an imbalance now in those states that  killed 
them off now. sf
